title: Grateful Dead Live at Uptown Theater on 1978-02-01
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried-> Me & My Uncle, Ramble On Rose, Cassidy, Sunrise, Sugaree

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, It Must Have Been The Roses, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drumz-> Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Around and Around

reviews.review_text: Nice recording! I wouldn't normally rate a show that had so much typical-78-quality (lazy) material on it with 5 stars, but this show is a big exception. The second set is one of the most musically wonderful moments of GD history you'll ever hear.

Chicago 2-1-78" This is. very surprising 78".The second set jam into The Other One is incredible and what the Dead are all about.Set 2 has some very exploratory jamming for 78".The show is definitely a must listen.

Milking the Turkey tease Check out the Milking the Turkey tease/jam starting around 3:04 during the Jam > Other One segment.  I agree this is a sleeper show that I would not normally pick based on the set list alone
